===[[Etymology]]===
Probably a [[neologism]] formed from [[success]] + [[-ism]]
===[[Noun]]===
#the ideology of striving or competition; achievement-orientation, self-help (e.g. nationalistic successism during the [[w:Meiji_Era|Meiji Era]] in Japan)
#the worship or idealization of success

===Example===

"''risshishugi'': successism, achievement-orientation, self-help" (in the glossary, at page 231 of ''A History of Japan - From Stone Age to Superpower'', by Kenneth G. Henshall, Palgrave)

